%% Figure 4 — The anti-hoarding money flow (primer §9).
%% Teaches: intake (progressive fees + demurrage, keyed to coin ancestry)
%% and outflow (burn + tilted per-block lottery) both anchor to the cluster
%% factor — the one wealth signal restructuring cannot forge.
flowchart TD
  FACT["Cluster factor — from the lineage's wealth, not the holder:<br/>1x small/diffuse · 3.5x at ~100,000 BTH · past 5x toward<br/>the 6x ceiling for million-BTH lineages"]:::anvil-warning

  subgraph INTAKE["Intake — priced by coin ancestry"]
    FEE["Progressive fees:<br/>per-byte base rate x cluster factor.<br/>Factor-1 users pay nano-BTH"]
    DEM["Demurrage when idle high-factor coins move:<br/>~2% of value after a year idle at factor 6;<br/>factor-1 coins exempt"]
  end

  FACT --> FEE
  FACT --> DEM

  FEES["Each block's collected fees<br/>(miners never receive fees — no MEV motive)"]
  FEE --> FEES
  DEM --> FEES

  BURN["20% burned — supply shrinks,<br/>a rebate to every holder equally"]:::anvil-muted
  POOL["Lottery pool"]
  FEES -- "20%" --> BURN
  FEES -- "80%" --> POOL

  EMIT["Scheduled slice of the block reward itself<br/>(ramping to 50%) — reaches wealth that<br/>never transacts"]
  EMIT --> POOL

  LOT["Per-block lottery: 4 randomly selected UTXOs,<br/>seeded by the previous finalized block's hash.<br/>Odds = value x inverse-factor tilt"]
  POOL --> LOT

  OUT["Small-lineage holders: per BTH, a factor-1 coin<br/>gets 6x the winning weight of a factor-6 coin.<br/>Splitting into a million UTXOs changes nothing"]:::anvil-success
  LOT --> OUT
